feat(api): :sparkles: add per-IP rate limiting middleware

Why:
The API lacks protection against abuse. A single client can make
unlimited requests, causing potential service degradation. Rate
limiting is essential for stability and fair resource allocation.

What:
Implement sliding window rate limiter middleware using Redis backend.
Configurable per request window (default 15 minutes) and max requests
(default 100). Returns 429 status with Retry-After header when limit
is exceeded. Middleware integrates seamlessly into Express routing.

Ticket: PROJ-312
Signed-off-by: Alice Developer <alice@example.com>
